news.title: Fraudulent transactions delays lender repayments of Aviom India Housing Finance
news.para: The housing finance company, founded by Kajal Ilmi, has built a loan book of Rs 1,752 crore by the end of March 2024 and catered to underserved masses with a focus on women borrowers.

news.title: R-Home's chairman and MD arrested for duping 200 flat buyers in Hyderabad
news.para: ​They collected Rs 48 crore from the customers in connection with the projects - Bliss Heights project in Ghatkesar, ORR Heights project in Patancheru, and Farmland project at Karamungi in Sangareddy district - which they promised to develop.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP proposes to narrow roads in seven sectors to make space for builder
news.para: The roads are supposed to be 75 metres wide under the Gurugram-Manesar Development Plan, which was approved in Nov 2012.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government to simplify building permission process
news.para: Chief Minister had given clear instructions to the Municipal Administration to streamline the process of granting permissions for the construction of buildings.

news.title: Odisha: ED seizes Rs 1.39 crore in raids linked to Z Estates
news.para: The search operation was carried out in places linked to an Odisha-based real estate company under the provision of the Foreign Exchange Management Act (FEMA), 1999.

news.title: Kalpataru gets Sebi's approval for Rs 1,590 crore IPO
news.para: Kalpataru and Unimech Aerospace are aiming to raise Rs 1,590 crore and Rs 500 crore, respectively, through their initial share sale offers.

news.title: BMC seizes 3,605 properties over unpaid tax in Mumbai
news.para: As per a release issued by the civic body, of the 3,605 properties, 1,767, the highest number, are in the western suburbs, 1,232 are in the island city, and 606 are in the eastern suburbs.

news.title: Commerce minister urges builders to adopt environment-friendly construction techniques
news.para: Addressing realtors' apex body CREDAI's 25th foundation day, the Union Commerce and Industry Minister also asked developers to build affordable rental housing projects to prevent the proliferation of slums in urban centres.

news.title: Sebi to auction 17 properties of KBCL India on December 23
news.para: The regulator has initiated the process for the sale of assets after KBCL India Ltd, its directors Rakesh Kumar, Vishvnath Pratap Singh and Shashi Kant Mishra failed to refund the investors' money.

news.title: ED raids three real estate firms in Delhi-NCR over alleged Rs 500 crore fraud
news.para: The searches pertain to companies such as Orris Infrastructure Private Limited, Greenbay Infrastructure Private Limited and Three C Shelter Private Limited and their promoters named Vijay Gupta, Amit Gupta, Sardar Nirmal Singh and some other directors, the sources said.

news.title: CREDAI urges govt for 100% home loan interest deduction to boost housing demand
news.para: CREDAI, which is celebrating 25th foundation day, also demanded that the definition of affordable housing should be revised, increasing the cap from Rs 45 lakh to at least Rs 75-80 lakh.

news.title: PropShare Platina to launch Rs 353 crore IPO on December 2
news.para: PropShare Platina is the first scheme of SM-REIT -- Property Share Investment Trust. The IPO, which is entirely a fresh issue of Platina units with no offer for sale (OFS) component, will conclude on December 4.

news.title: Rajasthan HC directs JDA to clear encroachments and remove squatters on public roads
news.para: During Thursday's hearing on a petition regarding road encroachments, JDA counsel Amit Kuri informed the court about existing encroachments from 200 feet Sirsi Road Bypass to Khatipura Tiraha and onwards to Queens Road.

news.title: Karnataka govt fails to clarify encroachment on Belagavi land: MoEF report
news.para: Clarification from the state was sought after a site inspection report by the Ministry showed that a portion of land offered by the Karnataka Forest Department for compensatory afforestation for a drinking water supply project in the state is under encroachment.

news.title: ACC and Ambuja Cements shares rise in early trade on November 25
news.para: The stock of Adani Energy Solutions jumped 6.89 per cent, Adani Green Energy soared 6.42 per cent, Adani Total Gas surged 5.33 per cent, Adani Ports climbed 4.64 per cent and Adani Power rallied 4.17 per cent on the BSE.

news.title: Prime minister to launch Neopolis IT township project in Thiruvananthapuram
news.para: The Neopolis project, part of the Union ministry of housing and urban affairs' broader vision, is one of eight such projects proposed across the country, with Thiruvananthapuram being the sole city selected from Kerala.

news.title: Global cement market to hit $592.38 billion by 2032, growing at 4.3% CAGR: Report
news.para: According to the World Cement Industry Outlook, global cement consumption is anticipated to rebound modestly, with growth expected to range between one per cent and two per cent.

news.title: Five lakh houses to be built for poor across urban and rural areas: Haryana CM
news.para: Additionally, under the Prime Minister's Housing Scheme, homes are being built for the poor, and Rs 80,000 is provided under the Dr. B.R. Ambedkar Housing Renovation Scheme for home repairs.

news.title: Nashik: 60% of Rs 140 crore property tax collected online by NMC
news.para: The civic body garnered property tax amounting to Rs 140 crore between April 1 and Nov 20 of the 2024-25 financial year. Out of Rs140 crore, Rs 84 crore was paid online by property owners (60%).

news.title: Jaipur development authority seals two illegal under-construction buildings on Kalwar Road
news.para: Officials said the builders constructed these two four-storied buildings with a basement, but without keeping the prescribed gangway on the ground floor and maintaining the mandatory separation gap with adjacent buildings.
